cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for recommendation systems in e-commerce, which involves processing sequential data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, since the paper focuses on the use of the Transformer model, which is a popular deep learning architecture for natural language processing tasks, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible because e-commerce recommendation systems often involve image processing and other AI techniques.
